The paper deals with the problem of predicting the exit of privately held companies using machine learning techniques. This falls under the domain of predictive analytics and machine learning, which is covered by the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also uses qualitative data and classifiers, which suggests that it may be relevant to the sub-categories cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CY (Computers and Society). Additionally, the paper deals with financial data and investment firms, which may be relevant to the sub-categories cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
